<section id="colours">
  <h2>臥室色彩指南</h2>
  <p>風水中的顏色與<a href="/wuxing/">五行</a>相對應。臥室適合使用促進休息、溫暖和親密感的色彩：</p>
  <table class="elements-table">
    <thead><tr><th>色系</th><th>元素</th><th>臥室效果</th><th>建議</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>柔粉色、桃色</td><td>火（柔和）</td><td>浪漫、溫暖、聯繫</td><td>非常適合伴侶</td></tr>
      <tr><td>米色、奶油色、赤陶色</td><td>土</td><td>穩定、扎根、滋養</td><td>最佳綜合選擇</td></tr>
      <tr><td>淺綠色、鼠尾草綠</td><td>木</td><td>成長、更新、平靜</td><td>適合療癒和休息</td></tr>
      <tr><td>淺灰色、白色</td><td>金</td><td>清晰、精確、清涼</td><td>少量使用；過多會感覺冰冷</td></tr>
      <tr><td>深藍色、黑色</td><td>水</td><td>深沉、內省、寒冷</td><td>避免作為主色調</td></tr>
      <tr><td>亮紅色、橙色</td><td>火（強烈）</td><td>刺激、熱情、躁動</td><td>僅作點綴；對睡眠過於活躍</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>您的個人元素（由<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>命盤決定）可以進一步細化這些建議。命中需要更多水元素的人可能受益於藍色點綴，而水過多的人則應完全避免。</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="colours">
  <h2>卧室色彩指南</h2>
  <p>风水中的颜色与<a href="/wuxing/">五行</a>相对应。卧室适合使用促进休息、温暖和亲密感的色彩：</p>
  <table class="elements-table">
    <thead><tr><th>色系</th><th>元素</th><th>卧室效果</th><th>建议</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>柔粉色、桃色</td><td>火（柔和）</td><td>浪漫、温暖、联系</td><td>非常适合伴侣</td></tr>
      <tr><td>米色、奶油色、赤陶色</td><td>土</td><td>稳定、扎根、滋养</td><td>最佳综合选择</td></tr>
      <tr><td>浅绿色、鼠尾草绿</td><td>木</td><td>成长、更新、平静</td><td>适合疗愈和休息</td></tr>
      <tr><td>浅灰色、白色</td><td>金</td><td>清晰、精确、清凉</td><td>少量使用；过多会感觉冰冷</td></tr>
      <tr><td>深蓝色、黑色</td><td>水</td><td>深沉、内省、寒冷</td><td>避免作为主色调</td></tr>
      <tr><td>亮红色、橙色</td><td>火（强烈）</td><td>刺激、热情、躁动</td><td>仅作点缀；对睡眠过于活跃</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>您的个人元素（由<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>命盘决定）可以进一步细化这些建议。命中需要更多水元素的人可能受益于蓝色点缀，而水过多的人则应完全避免。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="mirrors">
  <h2>Mirrors in the Bedroom</h2>
  <p>Mirrors are one of the most discussed feng shui topics. The classical position is clear: <strong>avoid mirrors that directly face the bed</strong>. The reasoning has several layers:</p>
  <p><strong>Energy bouncing:</strong> Mirrors reflect and amplify Qi. In a rest space, you want Qi to settle, not bounce. A mirror facing the bed creates a circuit of reflected energy that can disturb sleep.</p>
  <p><strong>The "third person" effect:</strong> In relationship feng shui, a mirror facing the bed symbolically introduces a third party into the partnership. Whether taken literally or as psychology, many practitioners report improved relationship harmony when bedroom mirrors are repositioned.</p>
  <p><strong>Practical compromise:</strong> Mirrors inside wardrobe doors, on a wall perpendicular to the bed (not facing it), or covered at night are all acceptable solutions. A vanity mirror across the room that does not reflect the bed while lying down is also fine.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="mirrors">
  <h2>臥室中的鏡子</h2>
  <p>鏡子是風水中討論最多的話題之一。傳統的立場非常明確：<strong>避免鏡子直接對著床</strong>。其理由有幾個層面：</p>
  <p><strong>能量反彈：</strong>鏡子反射並放大氣場。在休息空間中，您希望氣場沉靜，而非來回反彈。正對床的鏡子會形成反射能量的迴路，可能擾亂睡眠。</p>
  <p><strong>「第三者」效應：</strong>在感情風水中，正對床的鏡子象徵性地將第三方引入伴侶關係。無論從字面意義還是心理學角度理解，許多風水師都報告說，重新擺放臥室鏡子後，感情和諧度有所改善。</p>
  <p><strong>務實的折衷方案：</strong>將鏡子放在衣櫃門內、放在與床垂直的牆上（而非正對床），或在夜間遮蓋，都是可以接受的解決方案。房間另一側的梳妝鏡，只要躺下時不反射到床，也沒有問題。</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="mirrors">
  <h2>卧室中的镜子</h2>
  <p>镜子是风水中讨论最多的话题之一。传统的立场非常明确：<strong>避免镜子直接对着床</strong>。其理由有几个层面：</p>
  <p><strong>能量反弹：</strong>镜子反射并放大气场。在休息空间中，您希望气场沉静，而非来回反弹。正对床的镜子会形成反射能量的回路，可能扰乱睡眠。</p>
  <p><strong>「第三者」效应：</strong>在感情风水中，正对床的镜子象征性地将第三方引入伴侣关系。无论从字面意义还是心理学角度理解，许多风水师都报告说，重新摆放卧室镜子后，感情和谐度有所改善。</p>
  <p><strong>务实的折衷方案：</strong>将镜子放在衣柜门内、放在与床垂直的墙上（而非正对床），或在夜间遮盖，都是可以接受的解决方案。房间另一侧的梳妆镜，只要躺下时不反射到床，也没有问题。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="electronics">
  <h2>Electronics and Clutter</h2>
  <p>Classical feng shui cannot address smartphones &mdash; the texts predate them by centuries. But the underlying principle applies perfectly: <strong>the bedroom should contain only what supports rest and intimacy</strong>.</p>
  <p><strong>Screens:</strong> Televisions, laptops, and phones emit light and stimulate mental activity. Their presence converts a yin (rest) space into a yang (active) space. Moving screens out of the bedroom is the single most impactful change most people can make. If a phone must stay (as an alarm), place it face-down, across the room, in silent mode.</p>
  <p><strong>Under-bed storage:</strong> In feng shui, Qi circulates around and under the bed. Boxes, old clothes, and forgotten items stored under the bed create stagnant energy. If you must store items under the bed, keep them organised, in sealed containers, and limited to soft goods (linens, seasonal clothing) rather than emotional objects (old letters, memorabilia).</p>
  <p><strong>Clutter in general:</strong> Every item in the bedroom should earn its place. Books, work documents, exercise equipment, and laundry piles all carry active energy that competes with rest. A clean, minimal bedroom with good air circulation is the foundation of bedroom feng shui.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="electronics">
  <h2>電子產品與雜物</h2>
  <p>傳統風水無法針對智能手機提供建議——這些典籍比手機早了幾個世紀。但其底層原則完全適用：<strong>臥室應只擺放支持休息和親密關係的物品</strong>。</p>
  <p><strong>螢幕：</strong>電視、筆記型電腦和手機會發出光線並刺激大腦活動。它們的存在將陰（休息）空間轉變為陽（活躍）空間。將螢幕移出臥室是大多數人能做的最具效果的改變。如果手機必須留在臥室（作為鬧鐘），請將其螢幕朝下放置在房間另一端，並開啟靜音模式。</p>
  <p><strong>床下儲物：</strong>在風水中，氣在床的周圍和下方流通。床下堆放的箱子、舊衣物和遺忘的物品會產生停滯的能量。如果必須在床下儲物，請保持整齊，使用密封容器，並限於柔軟物品（床單、換季衣物），而非帶有情感的物品（舊信件、紀念品）。</p>
  <p><strong>整體雜物：</strong>臥室中的每件物品都應有其存在的理由。書籍、工作文件、運動器材和待洗衣物都攜帶著與休息相抗衡的活躍能量。一個整潔、簡約、空氣流通良好的臥室是臥室風水的基礎。</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="electronics">
  <h2>电子产品与杂物</h2>
  <p>传统风水无法针对智能手机提供建议——这些典籍比手机早了几个世纪。但其底层原则完全适用：<strong>卧室应只摆放支持休息和亲密关系的物品</strong>。</p>
  <p><strong>屏幕：</strong>电视、笔记本电脑和手机会发出光线并刺激大脑活动。它们的存在将阴（休息）空间转变为阳（活跃）空间。将屏幕移出卧室是大多数人能做的最具效果的改变。如果手机必须留在卧室（作为闹钟），请将其屏幕朝下放置在房间另一端，并开启静音模式。</p>
  <p><strong>床下储物：</strong>在风水中，气在床的周围和下方流通。床下堆放的箱子、旧衣物和遗忘的物品会产生停滞的能量。如果必须在床下储物，请保持整齐，使用密封容器，并限于柔软物品（床单、换季衣物），而非带有情感的物品（旧信件、纪念品）。</p>
  <p><strong>整体杂物：</strong>卧室中的每件物品都应有其存在的理由。书籍、工作文件、运动器材和待洗衣物都携带着与休息相抗衡的活跃能量。一个整洁、简约、空气流通良好的卧室是卧室风水的基础。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="elements">
  <h2>Five Elements in the Bedroom</h2>
  <p>A well-balanced bedroom incorporates all <a href="/wuxing/">five elements</a> in moderation, with an emphasis on Earth (stability) and gentle Fire (warmth):</p>
  <p><strong>Wood:</strong> Living plants (choose low-maintenance varieties that thrive in low light), wooden furniture, green accents. Avoid large or spiky plants; their yang energy is too active for sleep.</p>
  <p><strong>Fire:</strong> Candles (unscented or lightly scented), warm lighting, pink or red accent cushions. Avoid overhead spotlights and harsh lighting &mdash; these create excessive yang Fire.</p>
  <p><strong>Earth:</strong> Ceramics, stone, crystals (rose quartz is a traditional bedroom stone), square or flat shapes, earth-toned textiles. Earth is the most stabilising element for a bedroom.</p>
  <p><strong>Metal:</strong> Small metal picture frames, a clock, circular shapes. Metal should be present but not dominant &mdash; too much creates a cold, clinical atmosphere.</p>
  <p><strong>Water:</strong> A small water feature is calming but controversial in bedrooms. Excess Water can be too yin. If used, keep it small, clean, and placed away from the bed. Images of gentle water (not crashing waves) can substitute.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="elements">
  <h2>臥室中的五行</h2>
  <p>一個平衡良好的臥室應適度融入所有<a href="/wuxing/">五行</a>元素，重點放在土（穩定）和柔和的火（溫暖）上：</p>
  <p><strong>木：</strong>活體植物（選擇耐陰的低維護品種）、木質傢具、綠色點綴。避免大型或帶刺的植物；它們的陽氣對睡眠而言過於活躍。</p>
  <p><strong>火：</strong>蠟燭（無香或淡香）、暖色照明、粉色或紅色靠墊點綴。避免頂部射燈和刺眼的照明——這些會產生過多的陽火。</p>
  <p><strong>土：</strong>陶瓷、石材、水晶（粉晶是傳統的臥室石）、方形或平坦的造型、大地色調的紡織品。土是臥室中最具穩定作用的元素。</p>
  <p><strong>金：</strong>小型金屬相框、時鐘、圓形物品。金元素應存在但不宜主導——過多會營造冰冷、刻板的氛圍。</p>
  <p><strong>水：</strong>小型水景能帶來寧靜，但在臥室中頗具爭議。過多的水可能太過陰性。如果使用，應保持小巧、清潔，並遠離床鋪擺放。溫和流水的圖片（而非洶湧波浪）可以替代。</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="elements">
  <h2>卧室中的五行</h2>
  <p>一个平衡良好的卧室应适度融入所有<a href="/wuxing/">五行</a>元素，重点放在土（稳定）和柔和的火（温暖）上：</p>
  <p><strong>木：</strong>活体植物（选择耐阴的低维护品种）、木质家具、绿色点缀。避免大型或带刺的植物；它们的阳气对睡眠而言过于活跃。</p>
  <p><strong>火：</strong>蜡烛（无香或淡香）、暖色照明、粉色或红色靠垫点缀。避免顶部射灯和刺眼的照明——这些会产生过多的阳火。</p>
  <p><strong>土：</strong>陶瓷、石材、水晶（粉晶是传统的卧室石）、方形或平坦的造型、大地色调的纺织品。土是卧室中最具稳定作用的元素。</p>
  <p><strong>金：</strong>小型金属相框、时钟、圆形物品。金元素应存在但不宜主导——过多会营造冰冷、刻板的氛围。</p>
  <p><strong>水：</strong>小型水景能带来宁静，但在卧室中颇具争议。过多的水可能太过阴性。如果使用，应保持小巧、清洁，并远离床铺摆放。温和流水的图片（而非汹涌波浪）可以替代。</p>
</section>
</div>

<div class="lang-en">
<section id="mistakes">
  <h2>Common Bedroom Feng Shui Mistakes</h2>
  <p><strong>1. Bed under a window:</strong> The window behind the headboard means no mountain support. If unavoidable, use heavy curtains and a tall, solid headboard to compensate.</p>
  <p><strong>2. Bedroom as multi-use space:</strong> Working, exercising, and eating in the bedroom blurs its energetic purpose. The bedroom should be reserved for sleep and intimacy. A desk in the bedroom is particularly problematic &mdash; it brings career stress into your rest space.</p>
  <p><strong>3. Too much yang artwork:</strong> Dramatic landscapes, images of solitary figures, water scenes with waves, or bold abstract art create active energy. Choose calm, paired imagery &mdash; particularly for couples (two candles, two flowers, paired objects).</p>
  <p><strong>4. Sleeping in a "dead" corner:</strong> Rooms where the bed is positioned so that Qi stagnates (no air flow, far from the window, behind the door) create lethargy and health issues over time.</p>
  <p><strong>5. Ignoring the ceiling:</strong> Sloped ceilings, heavy light fixtures hanging above the bed, and dark ceiling colours all create downward pressure. If the ceiling slopes, place the bed under the highest point.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="mistakes">
  <h2>常見臥室風水錯誤</h2>
  <p><strong>1. 床在窗下：</strong>床頭板後面是窗戶意味著沒有靠山。若無法避免，可用厚重的窗簾和高大堅固的床頭板來彌補。</p>
  <p><strong>2. 臥室多功能化：</strong>在臥室中工作、運動和進食會模糊其能量用途。臥室應專用於睡眠和親密關係。臥室中放書桌尤其有問題——它會將事業壓力帶入您的休息空間。</p>
  <p><strong>3. 過多陽性藝術品：</strong>戲劇性的風景畫、獨身人物的圖像、帶有波浪的水景或大膽的抽象藝術會產生活躍能量。應選擇平和的、成對的意象——尤其對伴侶而言（兩支蠟燭、兩朵花、成對的物品）。</p>
  <p><strong>4. 睡在「死角」：</strong>床被擺放在氣場停滯的位置（無空氣流通、遠離窗戶、在門後方），久而久之會造成倦怠和健康問題。</p>
  <p><strong>5. 忽視天花板：</strong>傾斜的天花板、懸掛在床上方的沉重燈具以及深色天花板都會產生下壓感。如果天花板傾斜，應將床放在最高處的下方。</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
<section id="mistakes">
  <h2>常见卧室风水错误</h2>
  <p><strong>1. 床在窗下：</strong>床头板后面是窗户意味着没有靠山。若无法避免，可用厚重的窗帘和高大坚固的床头板来弥补。</p>
  <p><strong>2. 卧室多功能化：</strong>在卧室中工作、运动和进食会模糊其能量用途。卧室应专用于睡眠和亲密关系。卧室中放书桌尤其有问题——它会将事业压力带入您的休息空间。</p>
  <p><strong>3. 过多阳性艺术品：</strong>戏剧性的风景画、独身人物的图像、带有波浪的水景或大胆的抽象艺术会产生活跃能量。应选择平和的、成对的意象——尤其对伴侣而言（两支蜡烛、两朵花、成对的物品）。</p>
  <p><strong>4. 睡在「死角」：</strong>床被摆放在气场停滞的位置（无空气流通、远离窗户、在门后方），久而久之会造成倦怠和健康问题。</p>
  <p><strong>5. 忽视天花板：</strong>倾斜的天花板、悬挂在床上方的沉重灯具以及深色天花板都会产生下压感。如果天花板倾斜，应将床放在最高处的下方。</p>
</section>
</div>
